@niklas980408- I had the same problem... Here's what you do... Open the Call Of Duty file that was placed in your Applications Folder... Just like if you had inserted the DVD and opened it, A finder window opens with the separate files... (when you try to open the game with the application file, you get the 'Can't run the game off of DVD alert) You need to put the Files On your Hard Drive... To do this, all you have to do is Drag and Drop each file separately onto your Hard Drive's Icon in the upper right hand corner of the desktop... This copies the files to the Hard Drive... The new working files will be found in the finder window in Macintosh HD,(or whatever you may have renamed your HD) not in your applications folder... You can then move them to the applications folder if you like... Then Open the Game and Enjoy.... For anyone who doesn't see their Hard Drive Icon on the desktop, just go to finder preferences and check the box to show the HD on the desktop.... I'm running 10.7.2 Lion and the game works great... Thanx for the great upload... BTW, yeah I'm seeding....
